definition: to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be

sentences.english: Whether it is public or private.
sentences.chinese: 它是公共的还是私有的。

sentences.english: He should be grateful to the Fuehrer that he still has private property.
sentences.chinese: 他应该为自己还拥有私有财产而对元首感恩戴德。

sentences.english: It seems a bit idealist for me to think of money and private properties.
sentences.chinese: 我如此这般看待金钱和私有财产，似乎有些理想主义。

sentences.english: Greater disclosure requirements to answer to private-sector shareholders is significant.
sentences.chinese: 更大的披露要求对与私有部门的持股者来说意义重大。

sentences.english: The effort to privatize state-owned enterprises turned into an enrichment scheme for cronies of the regime.
sentences.chinese: 而国企私有化则成了政权姻亲的致富模式。

sentences.english: This is again a case of privatizing the gains and socializing the losses;
sentences.chinese: 这是又一次的私有化收益，公有化损失。

sentences.english: It is regard them as demesne belongings, regard as the furniture of adult.
sentences.chinese: 一是把他们当作私有财产，当作大人的附属品。

sentences.english: A new image is generated in your private catalog.
sentences.chinese: 在您的私有目录中生成了一个新的映像。

sentences.english: Select the image from your private catalog.
sentences.chinese: 从您的私有目录中选择镜像。

sentences.english: We learned all the tricks of privatization.
sentences.chinese: 我们学到了私有化的所有技巧。

sentences.english: But, concerning the very principle of private property, the Revolution always respected it.
sentences.chinese: 但是，大革命一直是尊重私有财产制度的原则的。

sentences.english: It protects private keys with a password.
sentences.chinese: 它通过密码保护私有密匙。

sentences.english: Safra Group is a privately held financial services and banking group.
sentences.chinese: 萨夫拉集团私有的金融服务公司和银行集团。

sentences.english: Private property is one; consent is the other.
sentences.chinese: 私有财产是第一个，同意是第二个。

sentences.english: In other words, you want the field to be private.
sentences.chinese: 换句话说，你希望字段是私有的。

sentences.english: Will the Private Cloud be a stepping stone towards the vision of Enterprise Cloud Computing?
sentences.chinese: 私有云是否会成为通往企业云计算的铺路石呢？
